Phase 4 — Response Schema Tests

- [ ] Create `ServiceEndpointContractTests.swift`.
- [ ] Add response-key assertions for movies, locations, seats, dates, purchases, login.
- [ ] Ensure assertions validate schema presence, not hard-coded production IDs.
- [ ] Add one negative test per domain using mocked non-2xx status to verify error mapping.

Phase 5 — Test Plan Wiring

- [ ] Update `SwiftCinemas.xctestplan` to unskip suite-level `SwiftCinemasTests`.
- [ ] Keep live smoke tests opt-in with skip guard unless `SWIFT_REST_LIVE_TESTS=1`.
- [ ] Verify test plan still targets `SwiftCinemas` app for variable expansion.
- [ ] Document mock mode as default in test plan usage notes.

Phase 6 — Legacy Test Cleanup

- [ ] Replace placeholder `@testable import YourAppModule` in `VenueForMoviesIntegrationTests.swift`.
- [ ] Remove invalid references (`AppServices.shared`, outdated model fields).
- [ ] Keep only meaningful integration coverage or retire file after replacement.

Phase 7 — Verification

- [ ] Run test plan locally and confirm new contract tests execute.
- [ ] Confirm failures print endpoint-specific diagnostics.
- [ ] Document test run modes (default mocked vs opt-in live) in Swift test docs/README.
- [ ] Verify both modes:
  - mocked mode: deterministic pass without backend
  - real mode: live smoke tests execute when env var is enabled
